Main development is done by Jörn Reder, but these developers (listed
in chronological order) contributed to the project with patches:

Norbert Preining <preining AT logic.at>
* 0.24 - Fast resizing bugfix
* 0.22 - Patch to make dvd::rip work with Perl 5.005

Doug Shea <doug_shea AT alumni.ucsd.edu>
* 0.31 - Alphabetical order for all generated file names

Martin Hill <mhill AT alumni.uwaterloo.ca>
* 0.38 - splitpipe.c fix, to compile on PPC architectures

Wolfgang Kinkeldei <kinkeldei AT nureg.de>
* 0.44 - "Show video from here" feature on Clip/Zoom page

Petros Stavrakakis <petros AT stavrakakis.de>
* 0.49 - cdrdao settings

Stefan Gmeiner <riddlebox AT freesurf.ch>
* 0.49 - ISO size estimation for on-the-fly burning

Christoph Bartoschek <bartoschek AT gmx.de>
* 0.49 - Frame range consideration for bitrate calculation

Matthias Riese <matthias.riese AT Uni-Bremen.DE>
* 0.49 - Pop existant re-opened single instance windows into foreground
       - DVD TOC: no fixed width but occupies all space available

Jarkko Hietaniemi <jhi AT iki.fi>
* 0.49 - To keep dvd::rip's dependencies low, I added Jarkko's
	 String::Scanf module to the distribution, moving it to
	 dvd::rip's namespace, so it can't conflict with an
	 existent original version.

Kianusch Sayah Karadji <kianusch AT sk-tech.net>
* 0.49 - Open/Close tray buttons on title and burn page
       - Volume scanning for chapter mode

Florin Andrei <florin AT andrei.myip.org>
* 0.50 - Comprehensive revision of the documentation fixing many
	 typos and grammatical flaws.

Jonathan Rogers <jonner AT mailandnews.com>
* 0.50 - OGG cluster mode for movies with more than one PSU.

Moritz Muehlenhoff <jmm AT informatik.uni-bremen.de>.
* 0.50 - Diskspace warning bugfix.
